# Dynamic Memory Strategy

Dynamic memory is enabled selectively to:
- improve overall host stability
- reduce idle memory consumption
- support temporary workload spikes
- maintain system responsiveness

Dynamic allocation will continue to be adjusted based on:
- workload behavior
- logging volume
- virtualization expansion
- future monitoring growth

